Ask HN: Password manager that doesn't suck?
text:
I want a password manager that does not "suck".

What I want/need:

* somehow integrates into iOS Safari

* somehow integrates into macOS Safari

* somehow integrates into Chrome

* somehow integrates into Android

* has password history (that is non-negotiable)

* isn't owned by shady company and pushes weird nonsensical features (VPN, antivirus, etc) or popups

* cares about synch for me (so no KeePass)

* ideally a bit secure

I am able to pay a bit, but not insanely much.
